63.8	Exposure_(photography)	Exposure (photography)	In photography, exposure is the total amount of light allowed to fall on the photographic medium during the process of taking a photograph. Exposure is measured in lux seconds, and can be computed from exposure value (EV) and scene luminance over a specified area.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Trailing_stars_above_Paranal.jpg/220px-Trailing_stars_above_Paranal.jpg
